<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><style>body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #1E1E2F; color: #E0E0E0; margin: 0; padding: 0; } .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 20px; background-color: #1E1E2F; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.2); } h1 { color: #FF6D00; margin-bottom: 10px; } h2 { color: #00BFA6; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 18px; } p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin: 8px 0; } ul { margin: 8px 0 8px 20px; } li { margin-bottom: 6px; } .section { background-color: #FFAB40; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 10px; color: #1E1E2F; } a.button { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 24px; margin-top: 20px; background-color: #FF6D00; color: #FFFFFF; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: bold; } .footer { font-size: 14px; color: #E0E0E0; margin-top: 20px; text-align: center; }</style></head><body><div class="container"><h1>Hello {{clientName}},</h1><p>I’m excited to report that the Email Service for Quest has been successfully implemented. All critical bugs in the previous setup have been resolved.</p><div class="section"><h2>Completed Tasks:</h2><ul><li>API endpoints for sending transactional emails created.</li><li>Implemented a template engine supporting dynamic HTML templates with generic parameters.</li><li>Emails can now be queued and processed reliably.</li></ul></div><p>The very email you are reading right now was sent using the new Email Service, demonstrating its ability to handle templates and dynamic content seamlessly.</p><p>I am confident this service will streamline all communications moving forward.</p><p>Best regards,<br>{{yourName}}</p><div class="footer">Quest Email Service</div></div></body></html>